            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section id="enforcement">
    <h2>6.3 Enforcement Layer</h2>
    <p>
      Safety invariants MUST be enforced in the RCAN runtime layer, <em>before</em> payloads reach
      application code or driver adapters. The enforcement order is:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Token validation</strong> (§5) — reject unauthenticated requests</li>
      <li><strong>Role &amp; scope check</strong> (§2) — reject insufficient privilege</li>
      <li><strong>Rate limiting</strong> (Invariant 4) — drop excess requests</li>
      <li><strong>Prompt injection scan</strong> (Invariant 7) — block suspicious NL instructions</li>
      <li><strong>Confidence gate</strong> (§16.2) — block or escalate low-confidence commands</li>
      <li><strong>HiTL gate</strong> (§16.3) — pause for human authorization if required</li>
      <li><strong>Audit log write</strong> (Invariant 3) — record before dispatch</li>
      <li><strong>Driver dispatch</strong> — only reached if all above pass</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="not-prose bg-yellow-500/5 border border-yellow-500/20 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
      <p class="text-sm"><strong class="text-yellow-400">Network loss:</strong> Invariant 2 requires that the robot
      monitors connection health. Implementations SHOULD use a heartbeat mechanism with a timeout of
      <code>latency_budget_ms × 2</code> before triggering safe-stop.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

